                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On the south wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Vṛishabhapurīśvara temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>Rājarāja I. Year 22: 1006-07 A.D.</p>						
                            
                            <p>This inscription commences with the <hi rend="italic">praśasti, Tirumagaḷ pōla</hi>, etc., of Rājarāja I.</p>						
                            
                            <p>It records the setting up of the image of Umā-Bhaṭṭāraki for god Āḍavallār, by Vaṇṇa[kkan Aiyā]ṟaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Chittirayāḷi, a member of the corps called <hi rend="italic">Janaṉāthatteriñja-valaṅgai Vēḷaikkāṟar</hi>, in the army of Śrī Rājarājadēva, and a Veḷḷāla resident in Ravikulamānikkapuram, in the eastern division of Śiṅgapura-nāḍu.</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
